    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on speed and favorable matchups to navigate a mixed bag of opposing arms. Our highest-scoring option is **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (74.43), whose elite sprint speed makes him an invaluable asset for our SB-weighted scoring. He draws a strong matchup against Myers (4.50 xERA), and despite the lower batting order slot, his dynamic platoon advantage generates our highest ceiling of the day. He is closely followed by **Junior Caminero** (70.99) and **Trea Turner** (70.45); **Trea Turner** remains a top-tier anchor against Holmes, benefiting from a 10% boost for hitting at the top of the order, while **Junior Caminero** capitalizes on a high-upside matchup against Keller. **Carson Benge** (67.24) and **Kyle Schwarber** (66.90) also present as high-value starts, with **Carson Benge** enjoying a significant 19% SP skill cushion against Assad.\n\nWhile our starters are well-positioned, the decision to bench **Josh Smith** (39.29) was the most difficult. He fell just short of our 40.0 floor due to a poor matchup against Woo, whose 3.30 xERA severely suppressed **Josh Smith**\u2019s efficiency rating. Elsewhere, we continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, and **Zac Veen**, who is currently holding in the minors. Managers should keep a close eye on **Gary Sanchez** (46.45) and **Victor Scott II** (46.01); while both are active, they are flirting with our bench threshold. **Victor Scott II** in particular carries a high risk-reward profile today, as his bottom-of-the-order placement penalizes his score despite his stolen base potential. Ensure lineup alerts are active for **Gary Sanchez**, as the SP skill adjustment against Eu P\u00e9rez leaves little margin for error.",
